data.chText: （通常为一时的）狂热，疯狂；风行一时的东西
data.enText: an enthusiastic interest in sth that is shared by many people but that usually does not last very long; a thing that people have a craze for

data.chText: 最近风靡全国的健身热
data.enText: the latest fitness craze to sweep the country

word_means: 使发狂；使现裂纹；出现裂纹

means: 使发狂；使(陶器)现裂纹；(陶器)出现裂纹

tr: a fine crack in a glaze or other surface
an interest followed with exaggerated zeal
example: he always follows the latest fads
it was all the rage that season

tr: develop a fine network of cracks

value.def: If there is a craze for something, it is very popular for a short time.

example.ex: Walking is the latest fitness craze.
example.tran: 散步是最近非常流行的健身方式。
